second song

So Family is calling, will we be stalling?

Baby is on the way

Temptations now are in full effect to move closer to family

Nothing as much is holding us here except benefits and some of the friendly faces we know.

I poked around and saw some nice paying jobs in Washington area,  my sister is starting her own ISP etc etc. 

will the land of the sun chase us away to visit rainy climates

will work start axing people because it's so slow as of late

will our realter find us a house before we even have made up our mind

stay tuned on the same bat channel, at the same inconsistant bat time for some very unknown updates to come,

(yeah, batman was cool)

A fork in the road approaches though many believe i am already at that forkk in the road.

Priority items- 

Family
House
Work

Work is 3rd on my priority list as far as current concerns and issues.   There are things i do need to address at some point, whether i will stay or not etc. etc. etc.    but going back to the start, family takes priority above all.   The balances in our bank account are staying at the same trends regardless of the changes so i am inclined to ignore any of the work aspects and move on.  I also need to be mindfull of the future.  My actions today will affect my decisions in 10 years.    So until all priorities are in order, work is a distant 3rd in my current priority list.

Day 1-

only 8 or so people asked a lot of questions-  piece of cake
very little training needed on my part
stress level......practically none
uncomfortable- not right now
natural competitive spirit-  being re-written to compensate

Any other actions on my part-  strangly- none.  loyalty to the company keeps me as well as future plans.  Since work and home are seperate(despite what everyone else says)  what is at work stays at work as far as stress or issues.

Not currently an option to leave- you know- catch 22 situations.  I don't think anything has occured to raise any anger level, haven't been really angry since that one time in 6th grade anyways.

Many are supportive and offer jobs elsewhere-  but that is not the option now-   looking for work has it's own hurdles anyways.  keeping options open?  of course-  but i guess i am a cautious individual.

So we are at a dichotemy between purchasing from two housing communities.

So far, they both are what we need.

Housing company 1-  very affordable, but we have to wait till august to by, then wait a year to move in......
Housing company 2- 6 months to move in maybe......but we may be eating cardboard for a while

decisions decisions

Most dragons are very wise, caring, and protective. It would make a person very lucky indeed to meet a dragon. Especially if they walked away untouched. Look at the reviews:

A truly amazing genre-breaking work of art unlike any that has ever been or ever will. I was captivated from the moment I opened the cover until the extremely suspenseful moment I turned the last page. With that said, I was a little disappointed that 71602 was knocked off by 92937 just as the plot was unfolding, but the arrival of 96240 really got my blood pumping and I just couldn't put the book down from that moment on.

I am so glad that Amazon.com is offering the "Search Inside This Book" option for this book so that it can be enjoyed by countless other avid readers who otherwise may not have come across it. I wait, impatiently, for the audio CD version of this fine book.


or this one

I've just read all the previous reviews with bewilderment. Is it a joke? None of you seem to understand what this book is actually about. It's not a narrative, a novel, or a story. It's an allegory, [...]

The author cunningly but unambiguously is drawing parallels between the study of number theory and the war on terror. How could anyone read this book all the way through and not spot it? I mean, even at the most superficial level any reader should see page after page of so called "random" numbers and immediately be thinking "cryptography", be thinking "qabala", be thinking "M15". Haven't *any* of you read "The Da Vinci Code"?

You only need to dig a little deeper to see the links to, oh where should I begin, how about Nostradamus? How about Freemasons? How about Al Qaeda? How about JERRY SPRINGER???

I explain all the hidden meanings in my unofficial "A Million Random Digits With 100,000 Normal Deviates" fan site http://blockcentral.com/

You may laugh as the hearse goes by
But you may be the next to die

They put you in a wooden box
Then cover you up with dirt and rocks

All goes well for a about a week
And then your coffin begins to leak

The worms crawl in, the worms crawl out,
In your stomache, and out your mouth,

Your stomach turns a mossy green,
and puss comes out your eyes like cocoa cream,

Your eyes will pop out of your head
And then you'll know your surely dead

So never laugh when a hearse goes by,
For you may be the next to die.

Just a typical evening-

Saw a musical episode of Xena- a bit much in the rock music department- otherwise humorous(free)<br>

Saw Ghost in the Shell 2- very artistic- nice- very confusing- yes(maybe I should have seen the first one)(15$)<br>
<br>
Had some popcorn that was a little off in the flavor department, but some wonderful mountain dew(6$)<br>
<br>
Heard the most humorous or demented cat story afterwards (Priceless and made the night)

Here is the story second hand, mayhap you will find the first hand account of this somewhere.... :)<br>
<br>
<br>
It started with an explanation that a cat got hit by a car- sad by all
accounts. The cat got hit and drove off i imagine, but not the
important part i would gather.  Of course being the dead of winter
the cat did have an issue of being frozen stiff.   At
this point some day or days later someone found this cat by the road
and found it quite sad,  the cat was promptly given a home in the
front yard- complete with a Christmas hat, and a Christmas
stocking, I understand there was a candy cane nearby as
well.  To say hi to the passers by- the paw was brought up so the
cat could say "hi".<br>
<br>
Humorous? maybe that's why i sometimes like black comedies myself I could guess.<br>
demented- yes- but i guess you had to hear the account out loud<br>

Here is a radom dream sequence for those that don't really care or really dislike dreams:

Characters: myself and 4-5 "extras"
Comedic Element: couple of squishy aliens

So here I am, wanding around a vacation house, minding my own business when these green squishy alien things come and kill people randomly.  no one else can see them.  they make it look like accidents.  they did die in creative ways though, involving acid and fire extinguishers, the plastic spikes swung from the cieling though was the most disturbing

Not going into detail about it, though i can say one thing.  It's odd that movies over dramatize blood, but in dreams, many times there is lack of blood(not that i am complaining mind you)
